    "attributes": {
        "action": "Requiring anyone to have a special licence for large knives in the UK",
        "additional_details": "Additionally ensure local councils or police  criminal background checks the applicants as well as mental health checks and waiting periods.\r\nMake it a criminal offence to sell, distribute, gift and supply a knife over the set limit of inches to anyone who does not have a licence\r\nExceptions,\r\nThere would need to be exceptions for household knives such as meat knives and other cooking knives in line with the 18+ laws.",
        "background": "Make the UK safer by having a licence that background checks people before purchasing large knives such as machetes would cut down knive crime in the UK by ensuring people who have no training, experience, or a professional use or collecting purposes getting hold of deadly knives.",
